<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/467a5b2b31aa682ef2b18afa5e20c8a3.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 7 and A = 5 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>80.0</li><li>80.3</li><li>85.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({5}\right)}}}=\frac{{7}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{7}}{{\tan{{\left({5}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{80.010366119329}\approx{80}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={7}^{{2}}+{80.010366119329}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={49}+{6401.6586865491}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={6450.6586865491}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{6450.6586865491}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{80.315992719689}\approx{80.3}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{5}^{\circ}\approx{85}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

